Second Lady Karen Pence, along with spouses of United States Senators, visited the Tracy's Kids Art Therapy Program at Children's National Health System in Washington, DC. They were greeted by hospital staff and proceeded to visit with young children and their families. Mrs. Pence gave the children coloring books and toured the art room. They also observed an art therapy session with pediatric patients undergoing cancer treatment and participated in a roundtable discussion with art therapists and hospital staff. Mrs. Pence has been a board member of Tracy's Kids since 2011 and was honored with the Courage Award in 2017 for her support of art therapy programs. The Tracy's Kids Art Therapy Program helps young cancer patients and their families cope with the emotional stress and trauma of cancer and its treatment. Children's National Health System is a pediatric academic health system that offers expert care and is ranked highly in various specialties.